.******************************************************************************
.* System         : ALL with screen painting.                                 *
.*                                                                            *
.* Include Name   : DSPFIELD.PBL                                              *
.*                                                                            *
.* Function       : Display any screen painted screen.                        *
.*                                                                            *
.* Author         : Phantom and Desert Storm                                  *
.*                                                                            *
.* Date Written   : 12/11/1991                                                *
.*                                                                            *
.* Parameters     : PRGID     DIM       8   program id                        *
.*                  SCRID     DIM       2   screen number                     *
.*                                                                            *
.* Ext. Routines  : DISPVARS - display the required variable on screen        *
.*                                                                            *
.* Returns        : EXIT = 1      no screen set up                            *
.*                                                                            *
.* Modifications  :                                                           *
.******************************************************************************
DSPFIELD  PACK      KEY15,PRGID,SCRID,SP20
          CALL      RSSCPS1                 * positional read
.
DSFLD100  CALL      RKSCPS1                 * next read
          BRANCH    OVRCD,DSFLD999          * end of file
.
          MATCH     PRGID,SCPSPID
          GOTO      DSFLD999 IF NOT EQUAL   * different program id
.
          MATCH     SCRID,SCPSSID
          GOTO      DSFLD999 IF NOT EQUAL   * different screen id
.
. ------- this is the routine each separate program needs -------
. ------- to set up the required variable                 -------
.
          CALL      DISPVARS                * move desired value into string
          GOTO      DSFLD100
.
DSFLD999  RETURN
+
